-- 888 to Appoint Mattingley as Permanent CEO, Times Says
-- B y   M a t h e w   C a r r
-- 2012-03-25T12:05:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-25/888-to-appoint-mattingley-as-permanent-ceo-times-says.html
Brian Mattingley, deputy chairman
of  888 Holdings Plc (888) , will become the permanent chief executive
officer of the U.K. online gambling company, the Sunday Times
 reported , without saying how it obtained the information.  Andrew Benbow, a spokesman for the company, declined to
comment on whether Mattingley will be placed into the role full
time, when contacted today by phone. “Brian has done an
exceptional job and I’m sure his appointment would be welcomed
by investors,” he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mathew Carr in London at 
 m.carr@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
